<p><a name="Notes" id="Notes"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Sonnet&amp;action=edit&amp;section=11" title="Edit section: Notes">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Notes</span></h2>
<div class="references-small">
<ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-0"><b><a href="#cite_ref-0" title="">^</a></b> Ernest Hatch Wilkins, <i>The invention of the sonnet, and other studies in Italian literature</i> (Rome: Edizioni di Storia e letteratura, 1959), 11-39</li>
<li id="cite_note-bertoni119-1">^ <a href="#cite_ref-bertoni119_1-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-bertoni119_1-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> Bertoni, 119.</li>
<li id="cite_note-2"><b><a href="#cite_ref-2" title="">^</a></b> <a href="/wiki/Philip_III_of_France" title="Philip III of France">Philip III of France</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-3"><b><a href="#cite_ref-3" title="">^</a></b> <a href="/wiki/Philip_IV_of_France" title="Philip IV of France">Philip the Fair</a> and <a href="/wiki/Charles_of_Valois" title="Charles of Valois">Charles of Valois</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-4"><b><a href="#cite_ref-4" title="">^</a></b> <a href="/wiki/Robert_II_of_Artois" title="Robert II of Artois">Robert II of Artois</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-5"><b><a href="#cite_ref-5" title="">^</a></b> <a href="/wiki/Edward_I_of_England" title="Edward I of England">Edward I of England</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-6"><b><a href="#cite_ref-6" title="">^</a></b> <a href="/wiki/Alfonso_X_of_Castile" title="Alfonso X of Castile">Alfonso X of Castile</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-7"><b><a href="#cite_ref-7" title="">^</a></b> Folger's Edition of "Romeo and Juliet"</li>
</ol>
</div>
